TEXT 96 448 Left 3 ; Signal sources and default values
TEXT 1856 448 Left 3 ; Relay wire-break gating / OR merge
TEXT 3952 448 Left 3 ; Red voltage judgement
TEXT 4032 1008 Left 3 ; Green voltage judgement + relay actual AND
TEXT 2616 1744 Left 3 ; Wire-break latch / POR reset
TEXT 5776 448 Left 3 ; Red flashing lamp circuit
TEXT 5776 1488 Left 3 ; Red / green power modules
TEXT 96 3624 Left 3 ; Timing testbench and expected behaviour
TEXT 424 2440 Left 1 ; Defaults: DISCONNECT/SHOULD use pull-up style; ACTUAL uses pull-down style. VREF_0P6_R/G are 0.6 V comparator references.
TEXT 2024 1344 Left 1 ; REL_FAULT_SET = (MAINP_DISC&SHOULD) OR (MAINN_DISC&SHOULD) OR (PRE_DISC&SHOULD)
TEXT 4128 808 Left 1 ; TL331 output is open collector. High on N1N12 releases NE555 RESET and enables red flash.
TEXT 4104 1584 Left 1 ; V_SAFE AND MAINP_ACTUAL AND MAINN_ACTUAL AND PRE_ACTUAL AND LATCH_OK -> green MOS gate.
TEXT 2720 2960 Left 1 ; POR fixed in current netlist: C18/R55 -> R64 -> U20.A; U20.Y=N1N198 reset pulse. N1N93=LATCH_OK.
TEXT 5904 1288 Left 1 ; 555 flash output drives AO3480C low-side sink RED_OUT_K.
TEXT 5904 2680 Left 1 ; +5VR powers red comparator/555; +5VG powers green comparator/logic/latch.
TEXT 3600 3904 Left 2 ; Expected timing: 0-20ms safe/no fault -> green ON after POR. 25-60ms V_CONTROLLER>0.6 -> red flashes.
TEXT 3600 3984 Left 2 ; 40-55ms V_BATTERY>0.6 -> green OFF. 81-100ms MAINP_ACTUAL=0 -> green OFF.
TEXT 3600 4064 Left 2 ; 120-130ms MAINP_DISCONNECT=1 while SHOULD=1 -> latch trips; green remains OFF after input clears.
TEXT 3600 4144 Left 2 ; 161-176ms LVS power cycle -> POR reset clears latch; 210-220ms V_DISCONNECT=1 -> latch trips again.
TEXT 3600 4224 Left 2 ; Plot: V(RED_OUT_K), V(GREEN_OUT_K), V(N1N12), V(V_SAFE), V(REL_FAULT_SET), V(N1N198), V(N1N93).
